1801:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc.c **** /**
1802:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @brief  Wait until the RTC Time and Date registers (RTC_TR and RTC_DR) are
1803:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         synchronized with RTC APB clock.
1804:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @note   The RTC Resynchronization mode is write protected, use the
1805:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         __HAL_RTC_WRITEPROTECTION_DISABLE() before calling this function.
1806:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @note   To read the calendar through the shadow registers after Calendar
1807:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         initialization, calendar update or after wakeup from low power modes
1808:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         the software must first clear the RSF flag.
1809:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         The software must then wait until it is set again before reading
1810:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         the calendar, which means that the calendar registers have been
1811:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         correctly copied into the RTC_TR and RTC_DR shadow registers.
